FBIS4-59657 "drnes095_j_94004" FBIS-NES-94-095 Daily Report 16 May 1994 ARAB PENINSULA Saudi Arabia Police Keep Watchful Eye on Iran's Hajj Headquarters Police Keep Watchful Eye on Iran's Hajj Headquarters Headquarters Active Despite Restrictions LD1605120294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 16 May 94 LD1605120294 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] The third conference on Ahl al-Bayt -- peace be upon them -- was held today at the esteemed leader's headquarters in holy Mecca. Our correspondent in Mecca sent the following report: [Unidentified correspondent] Dear listeners of the midday news bulletin of the Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran [IRI], I am speaking to you from the esteemed leader's headquarters in holy Mecca. The third Ahl al-Bayt conference was held here today, attended by a group of cultural, scientific, and religious personalities from Iran and other Islamic countries. Various speakers from the IRI, Iraq, Afghanistan, Nigeria, Turkey, Azerbaijan and the United States addressed the audience on the social circumstances of the Ahl al-Bayt followers throughout the world, and their struggle against tyranny and dictatorship. Despite the restrictions imposed by the Saudi police, the esteemed leader's headquarters is witnessing a constant flow of Iranian and non-Iranian pilgrims, and the ceremonies held inside the headquarters are warmly welcomed.
